<dl id="n01042a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01042a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01042a"> 42(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> leitmotivs no 0 d&eacute;cor id&eacute;al</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">l&apos;Op&eacute;ra, nous dit-il, nous demandons, en moyenne, huit minutes pour un changement de <mark>d&eacute;cor</mark> entre le baisser et le lever du rideau. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Mais, hormis les cas assez rares o&ugrave; on veut repr&eacute;senter la mer ou le d&eacute;sert, la sup&eacute;riorit&eacute; du fond panoramique ne para&icirc;t pas absolue. <br><font color="green">[In opera, he tells us, we require on average eight minutes for the scenery to change between the lowering and raising of the curtain. [&hellip;]</font> But, beyond the fairly rare situations where we want to represent the sea or the desert, the importance of the panoramic backdrop does not seem absolute.] <small> <a name="IL11nov22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IL11nov22"><cite title="source">L'Illustration</cite></a> (11 November 1922) 462/3-463/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05117k" href="c05all.htm#c05117k">VI.C.05:117(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
